SIMPLE: presphenoid
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Presphenoid
<hw>Pre*sphe"noid</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <fld>(Anat.)</fld>
<def>Situated in front of the sphenoid bone; of or pertaining to the
anterior part of the sphenoid bone (<it>i. e.</it>, the presphenoid
bone).</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Presphenoid bone</b></col> <fld>(Anat.)</fld>, <cd>the
anterior part of the body of the sphenoid bone in front of the
basisphenoid. It is usually a separate bone in the young or fetus, but
becomes a part of the sphenoid in the adult.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Presphenoid</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Presphenoid
<hw>Pre*sphe"noid</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Anat.)</fld> <def>The
presphenoid bone.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Presphenoidal</ent>⟦br⟧
